lp desk       my.UIC       Campus resources       Resources quick sheet       Committees                  AHS Awards   View awards guidelines and submit your nomination            AHS Office of Research   Dedicated to supporting AHS researchers            Human Resources   Find information and resources to answer some of your most common human resource questions           Faculty resources        UIC promotion and tenure resources   View promotion and tenure forms, a calendar of important deadlines and more         AHS Promotion and Tenure Guidelines   Outlines AHS faculty appointments and promotion and tenure standards         AHS peer evaluation procedures   General expectations and guidelines         AHS faculty bylaws   Bylaws of the AHS faculty         AHS teaching load policy   Guidance in making AHS teaching assignments         UIC Faculty Affairs   Information and resources for faculty careers         AHS Clinical Fieldwork Placement Policies   Policy related to participation in clinical, fieldwork, experiential learning or professional training rotations/internships         Responding to Student Misconduct: Procedural Guidelines   Report suspected and actual violations of the University’s Standards of Conduct for students         Responding to Students Exhibiting Signs Emotional Distress: Procedural Guidelines   Take action to assist students reporting or exhibiting signs of stress or emotional distress         UIC Academic Affairs   Academic policies, priorities and initiatives                     AHS Faculty Mentoring Program  The AHS Faculty Mentoring Program supports junior faculty with their career development through mentorship from faculty within and outside of their respective academic departments. Junior faculty are strongly encouraged to attend mentoring introduction workshops, which are held twice a year. New faculty are invited to attend by the dean’s office.   AHS faculty mentoring guidebook       AAMC compact between postdocs and mentors    6 things every mentor should do       AHS Clinical and Experiential/Fieldwork Education Resources   Working handbook to clinical education:  Clinical Education Handbook  What to send to a site requesting a certificate of insurance for UIC:  Liability self-insurance plan  Sample certificate of coverage  What to send to the Dean’s office:  Fieldwork request form  What to send to a site to invite them to use the UIC student placement agreement template:  SPA cover letter template  Agreement UIC student placement practice settings (pdf)  Agreement UIC student placement practice settings (MS Word)  What to send to a site requesting a certificate of coverage for a student or students:  COC request form for student proof of coverage  What to send to the dean’s office for HIPPA-related training and bloodborne pathogens training requests:  LMS account request template  Email template LMS training modules for students      Student Success Series   At the start of 2019, AHS produced three lunchtime talks centered on student success. Find links to the presentations below.        Student Success Lunch Series 1   Getting to Know our AHS Undergraduate Students         Student Success Lunch Series 2   AHS Advisor Narrative. Understanding how undergraduate advisors assist faculty in facilitating student success and vice versa         Student Success Lunch Series 3   Career Relevance in our Courses                Inside AHS    Back to main content           Faculty and Staff Resources    Expand Faculty and Staff Resources menu          AHS Awards    Communications    Human Resources    Office of Research    Expand Office of Research menu          Proposal Development    AHS Approval    External Review    IRB Applications    Poster Printing    AHS Interdisciplinary Pilot Grant Program    Expand AHS Interdisciplinary Pilot Grant Program menu          AHS Interdisciplinary Pilot Grant recipients      Funding Agency Newsletters        Student Resources    Expand Student Resources menu     